§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A set $C ⊂ 𝗥^n$ is a ❬cone❭ (or ❬nonegative homogeneous❭)
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ x ∈ C \text{ and } θ ≥ 0 ⇒ θx ∈ C. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§§ Examples ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $x ∈ 𝗥^n$. Define $C_1 \subset 𝗥^n$ by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ C_1 = \Set{θx}{θ ≥ θ}. ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ $C_1$ is a cone. ⦉

  ‖ The set
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ C_2 = \Set{x ∈ 𝗥^{n}}{x_i ≥ 0 \text{ for } i = 1, …,
        n} ⦉
    ⦉
    is a cone. ⦉

  ‖ $C_2$ is called the ❬non-negative orthant❭. ⦉

  ‖ The set
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ C_3 = \Set{x ∈ 𝗥^{n}}{x_i ≤ 0 \text{ for } i = 1, …,
        n} ⦉
    ⦉
    is a cone. ⦉

  ‖ The set $C_2 ∪ C_3$ is a cone. ⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the nonnegative orthant of $\R^n$ by $𝗥^n_+$. ⦉

  ‖ We denote the nonpositive orthant of $\R^n$ by $𝗥^n_-$. ⦉
⦉

